text.tspan: * SUPERDRACO ENGINES ARE NOT VISIBLE FROM TOP OR BOTTOM OF VEHICLE
CONTAINS FUEL FOR TWO SUPERDRACO ENGINES AND FOUR DRACO THRUSTERS
NARROW STANCE OF REAR LEGS PROVIDES MORE SUPPORT FOR LAND PARACHUTE LANDINGS
THE FOUR MAIN PARACHUTES ARE ATTACHED ABOVE THE FRONT DOOR; BECAUSE OF THIS,
THE VEHICLE LEANS BACK WHEN PARACHUTES ARE DEPLOYED. THE SPACING OF THE REAR
LANDING LEGS HELPS CUSHION THE VEHICLE WHEN TOUCHING DOWN ON SOLID GROUND
REAR OF VEHICLE FACES TOWARDS THE SUN AND HAS NO WINDOWS
USED TO ENTER AND EXIT THE VEHICLE WHILE ON EARTH
USED TO DOCK WITH THE ISS
USED FOR ATTITUDE CONTROL IN SPACE
USED FOR LAUNCH ABORT AND PROPULSIVE LANDING
